* {{ill|Empress Jingū|en|Empress Jingū|qid=Q232803|lt=Jingū Kōgō|1=Empress Jingū}}
* {{ill|Himegami|lt=Himegami|lt=Hime Ōkami|ja|姫大神|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hime Ōkami|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 比売神}}

=== Merged Shrines ===
* The {{ill|Minamino Shrine|ja|南小野神社|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Minamino Shrine|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} (a former village shrine) is also merged here. Note that Minamino Shrine merged with {{ill|Kumanoza Shrine|ja|熊野座神社|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kumanoza Shrine|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} in {{ill|1910|en|1910|qid=Q2075|lt=1910 AD|1=1910}} (Meiji 43).
** The enshrined deities of Minamino Shrine and Kumanoza Shrine are: {{ill|Isotake no Mikoto|ja|五十猛命|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Isotake no Mikoto|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 五十猛神|1=Isotakeru-no-Mikoto|2=ja|3=五十猛神|4=zh|5=五十猛神}}, {{ill|Ōi-hime no Mikoto|ja|王位姫命|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōi-hime no Mikoto|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}, {{ill|Izanami-no-Mikoto|ja|伊弉冉命|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Izanami-no-Mikoto|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to イザナミ|1=Izanami|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q682306}}, {{ill|Kototoki no Otoko|ja|事解之男命|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kototoki no Otoko|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 熊野権現|1=Kumano Gongen|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q11568925}}, {{ill|Hayatama Otoko|ja|速玉男命|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hayatama Otoko|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 熊野権現|1=Kumano Gongen|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q11568925}}, and {{ill|Empress Jingū|en|Empress Jingū|qid=Q232803|lt=Jingū Kōgō|1=Empress Jingū}}.

== Worship and Belief ==
* The annual festival day is {{ill|October 15|en|October 15|qid=Q2919|lt=October 15|1=October 15}}.

== Subordinate Shrines ==
* An Inari shrine dedicated to {{ill|Ukanomitama|en|Ukanomitama|qid=Q3080728|qid=Q3080728|lt=Ukanomitama|1=Ukanomitama}} is located within the shrine grounds.

